FBIS4-17881 "drsov082_a_94043" FBIS-SOV-94-082 Daily Report 26 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Israeli Prime Minister Wraps Up Visit to Russia Israeli Prime Minister Wraps Up Visit to Russia Rabin Condemns Hamas LD2604172194 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 1500 GMT 26 Apr 94 LD2604172194 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy Russian BFN [Text] Today, Yitzhaq Rabin told a group of journalists in Moscow that there continues to be a major chance of implementing the Near East peace process. Yitzhaq Rabin noted: [Begin Rabin recording, in Hebrew, with superimposed Russian translation] At all events there is no doubt that public support for the peace process and agreement with the PLO [brief break in transmission] a consequence of certain political views. This is the natural result of the disillusionment of very many of our people. People are disappointed that, while the talks seem to be continuing, the number of terrorist acts is not only not declining but, in terms of the number of casualties...[pauses] More and more people are suffering. This is a direct result of the fact that Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] and the Islamic Jihad, which are responsible for this terror, are headed by extremists and religious fanatics, who will go to any lengths to strangle the peace process. [end recording]
